<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-28T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-28T14:00:00-05:00" n="969" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d969">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9728: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-28T15:00:00-04:00">August 28, 1937—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>190. Shanghai’s 583, August 27, 6 p.m. In the opinion of the Department
                            this is a point which you might if opportunity affords mention casually
                            and orally to high officials of the Chinese Government as one appearing
                            to warrant serious consideration.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>